        &lt;h2&gt;Directory Structure&lt;span class=&#34;absolute -mt-20&#34; id=&#34;directory-structure&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#directory-structure&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default, Hugo searches for Markdown files in the &lt;code&gt;content&lt;/code&gt; directory, and the structure of the directory determines the final output structure of your website.
Take this site as an example:&lt;/p&gt;
